title: Link Failures & Page Failures
content:
I have been a Firefox user pretty much since it was first released, raved about it to anyone who would listen & generally encouraged friends etc. to switch.

However, since the last update, now on 141.0 64 bit on Windows 11, I find myself using my backup browser -Opera - more & more, even though generally I have always considered it a much lesser browser than Firefox.

Two main reasons for this:

1. Firefox is set to open links in a new Tab - when I click on a link the Tab opens, the little circle-y thing goes round & round for 10-30 seconds, & then - absolutely nothing, just a blank Tab. If I close the Tab before it's finished 'loading' & try the link again - the same thing happens. If I wait till it's finished 'loading' &try the link again it will open th enew Tab & load the page successfully. This doesn't happen every time but definitely over 50% of the time.

2. When using YouTube, search pages will start to load the video thumbnails but then stop after a variable number - the thumbnail titles & link are visible & usable but where the thumbnail should be is just a placeholder. This happens practically all the time & requires multiple page reloads to correct it, & even that doesn't work sometimes.

3. I've had to use Opera to post this as Firefox would not let me access my Mozilla account

I have not added any new extensions since that last upgrade.

Neither of these issues arise when I use Opera so it's obviously not a connectivity or bandwith issue.

I'd be grateful if these issues could be corrected as Opera does not have all the functionality that I like in Firefox but it also doesn't drive me crazy with these issues.

Thanks

title: Firefox Lag and Video Stuttering on StudyStream Website with Multiple Video Streams
content:
While using the StudyStream website on Mozilla Firefox, I‚Äôm experiencing significant performance issues when multiple users have their cameras turned on.

Symptoms include: 

   Real-time video lags and stutters noticeably. 
   Video feeds take several seconds to load or appear. 
   The stream is not smooth, making the experience frustrating during group sessions.

Additional Notes: 

   This issue only occurs on Firefox. The same website works smoothly with no noticeable lag on other browsers such as Google Chrome and Microsoft Edge. 
   My Firefox is updated to the latest version. 
   The problem persists even after disabling extensions and trying in a private window.

It appears that Firefox may be struggling with handling multiple simultaneous video streams on this specific site. Any guidance or fixes would be appreciated.
